        "compare_principle": "Step 1: Change the environment",
        "step2_label": "Step 2: Notice the difference after 5 min",
        "acc_why_label": "Why It Matters",
        "acc_why_body": "<p>Inside a sealed glove, humidity passes 90% within minutes and skin temperature holds around 35°C for the rest of the shift.</p><p>German TRGS 401 classifies more than two hours a day in occlusive gloves as wet work — a recognised occupational hazard. EV and HV technicians run three to six hours per shift.</p><p>Skin that stays wet softens and swells. Wet skin is more permeable than dry skin.</p><p>DRYE keeps skin drier. That's the whole intervention.</p>",
        "acc_specs_label": "Specifications",
        "acc_maker_label": "Who Makes This",
        "maker_image": "shopify://shop_images/granqvists-today-683x1024_b98fa9ce-5637-4428-887e-70f3d888ca05.jpg",
        "acc_maker_body": "<p>Made by Granqvists Gloves AB, Karlstad, Sweden — a glove manufacturer since 1984. The same production unit has supplied roughly 80% of military gloves to the Swedish, Norwegian and Finnish armed forces. ISO 9001 and ISO 14001 certified. Fabric knitted in Sweden by Trikåby. Sewn in the EU.</p>",
        "acc_how_label": "How It Works",
        "acc_how_body": "<p>Your glove still does the protecting. DRYE changes what touches your skin — a thin dry layer between your hand and the nitrile, latex, rubber or sealed work glove.</p><p>Every liner that absorbs has a saturation point. Once it fills, it becomes the wet layer against your skin. DRYE routes moisture outward instead. The skin side is built not to hold sweat, so it has no saturation point.<br/>##image11##</p><p>One fabric, knitted in one operation. Two surfaces. One direction. No coatings, no chemicals, no membranes.</p>",
        "acc_sizing_label": "Sizing And Fit",
        "acc_sizing_body": "<h5>How it should feel</h5><p>Snug, like a second skin. You should feel the fabric, not the seams. If it's tight across the back of the hand, size up. Circumference decides — not finger length.</p><h5>Putting them on</h5><p>The fabric is 0.4 mm. Pull them on gently, finger by finger. Do not yank them on the way you would an outer glove — that puts all the load on the thumb and finger seams.</p><h5>Taking them off</h5><p>Go slow. Peel finger by finger rather than pulling from the cuff.</p><h5>Washing</h5><p>Machine wash up to 90°C. They do not shrink and nothing washes out — there are no coatings or finishes to lose.</p>",
        "acc_shipping_label": "Shipping And Returns",
        "acc_shipping_body": "<h5>The Glove-Off Test — 60 days</h5><p>Wear them one full shift under your sealed glove. If your skin isn't drier when the glove comes off, keep the liners and we refund every dollar. Sending a worn pair back from the US costs more than the pair is worth. No forms, no return shipping.</p><h5>Wrong size?</h5><p>If you measured against our guide and it still doesn't fit, we ship the correct size at no cost.</p><h5>Ships from Sweden</h5><p>10–14 business days to the US with PostNord, no import charges at delivery. UPS is faster but the recipient pays brokerage and duty.<br/><br/>Ships from Sweden<br/><br/>Which shipping option should I choose?<br/><br/>USA- PostNord: 4–6 business days. No import charges at delivery.- UPS: 1–3 business days. Import charges are paid by the recipient.Canada- PostNord: 4–6 business days. Taxes and a CAD 9.95 handling fee may apply.- UPS: 1–3 business days. Taxes and UPS import fees may apply.<a href=\"https://www.dryeliner.com/pages/policy\">View full shipping policy</a></p><p><a href=\"#drye-faq\">Full shipping and returns policy → See the FAQ below</a></p>",
        "low_stock_threshold": 10,
